<br>
Similarly-priced horses and lizards are the same speed, and<br>
take just as long to start and stop.<br>
<br>
All race/class combos can buy horses and lizards.  Make<br>
sure your charisma is at least 110 or so when you buy;<br>
higher charisma doesn't help with prices.<br>
<br>
On a horse or lizard, you med while you're not moving.<br>
You can also cast while you're not moving... So standing<br>
still on a horse lets you med continuously, even while<br>
casting, and lets you avoid sit agro.<br>
<br>
The horse head is really annoying and can make it very<br>
difficult to target mobs and players.  To see it for yourself<br>
before you buy, find a horse owner who's your race and<br>
Bind Sight on him or her.  You used to be able to solve the<br>
horse-head problem by simply turning new models off, but<br>
no longer.<br>
<br>
Color doesn't affect speed; it's drum size for lizards and<br>
bridle material for horses.<br>
<br>
To &quot;sell back&quot; a horse, hail the stablehands until you find<br>
the one who takes your bridle type.  Give (don't sell) him<br>
your bridle, and he'll give you a Bag of Platinum in return.<br>
Make sure your charisma is buffed to at least 110 or so,<br>
then sell the Bag to any NPC merchant; you'll receive about<br>
70 percent of what you originally paid for the horse.<br>
Lizards work the same way.<br>
<br>
<br>
More info on horses/lizards is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/editorials/horses.asp">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
